Customer Reviews

Yes. It cheats. From addicted to deleted in 1 week.


   by 13110511

   At first, I thought I was a sore loser so I kept playing to build more
   character. But it seemed, after one game where I beat the AI when it
   still had a chit on my side (a 3 point win for the round) ... it
   suddenly began rolling multiple doubles, trapping me on EVERY game so I
   couldn't re-enter the board, and always (no exception) rolling exactly
   what it needed. The only way to win a round is to plan on it cheating
   ... it works. It's funny, though, it really was as if the AI was
   throwing a tantrum ... but I suspect it was because I ignored ALL of
   the advertisements. It must be programmed to discourage you from
   playing backgammon so you'll try Yahtzee or any of the other games it
   advertises. Loved it at first ... but deleted when I had to admit it
   really is cheating.

It cheats, pure and simple.


   by T. Manning

   I just read a review that I can't disagree with: this game cheats. You
   can guarantee that whenever the computer opponent needs a certain
   number, it's going to get it. And you will not get what you need. No
   matter how smart you are, no matter how well you plan your defensive
   strategies or offensive strategies, you will not beat this computer
   more than once every so often. I downloaded it so I can learn how to
   play, but all I've learned is how to lose to the computer. It's very
   frustrating. That said, it's a beautifully rendered game. I just wish
   the computer opponent was more fair.

Good app


   by Spring:-))

   After many years of not playing backgammon I decided to get back into
   the game by practicing using this app. I like this app because the
   graphics are not ornate and distracting. However it appears to me that
   when the single play option is used the computer has an unfair
   advantage and consistently recovers double rolls. The dice roll results
   do not appear as random and seem to meet the needs of the computer's
   game. However the online option is excellent. The rolls appear random
   and the opponent selected is of equal expertise.

